# Backend Performance

> General performance principles: see `core/engineering.mdc`.
> Pagination, indexes, `select`: see `prisma.mdc`.

## Database Queries

- Avoid unnecessary round-trips — do not query the same entity twice in one request
- Prefer one well-structured query over multiple simple ones when it reduces latency
- Watch for **N+1 queries** — use Prisma `include` / `select` with relations, or batch with `findMany` + `in`

```ts
// ❌ N+1 — query per todo
for (const todo of todos) {
  await this.prisma.comment.findMany({ where: { todoId: todo.id } });
}

// ✅ single query
await this.prisma.todo.findMany({
  include: { comments: true },
});
```

## When to Optimize

Do not optimize without evidence. But always avoid patterns that are **obviously** inefficient:

- Loading full tables into memory
- Queries inside loops
- Unbounded list responses (see `prisma.mdc` for pagination)
